    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Double pieces of plate armor for the pauldron, worn to reinforce the lower three-quarters of the front of the pauldron and attached to it by pins, pegs, or rivets; first appeared in the early 15th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
